To jazz up your meat-free Mondays, nothing helps a salad like a good helping of cheese, basil vinaigrette, some chopped nuts and a helping of fresh herbs, particularly from this nectarine mozzarella salad.   This nectarine, mozzarella salad is healthy and has some crunch, sweetness and a slight hint of spice.  This recipe is courtesy of the cookbook Sam Linsell and it has been described as a flavour bomb.  ALSO READ: Recipe of the day: Mediterranean okra stew This recipe from Sam Linsell courtesy of juicydelicious.co.za.